    <releases>
        <release version="5.9.0" date="2021-01-28">
            <description>
                <p>New features:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Extractors</li>
                    <li>Using MPICH ABI compatible implementation</li>
                    <li>Python2 no longer supported</li>
                    <li>Fast preselection</li>
                    <li>Choosing DISPLAY or EGL device using command-line arguments</li>
                    <li>Launcher arguments for using mesa</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Enhancements:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ray tracing updates</li>
                    <li>NVIDIA IndeX plugin improvements</li>
                    <li>Volume rendering of rectilinear grids</li>
                    <li>Volume rendering with blanking of uniform grids</li>
                    <li>Volume rendering multiblock datasets with 3D uniform grids</li>
                    <li>Volume rendering with a separate opacity array</li>
                    <li>Custom opacity array ranges</li>
                    <li>Improvements to ordered compositing</li>
                    <li>Opacity Editor Freehand Drawing</li>
                    <li>Faithful rendering of meshes with significantly different cell sizes</li>
                    <li>Tone mapping and screen space ambient occlusion</li>
                    <li>Edge Tint in physically-based rendering</li>
                    <li>Rendering array selection</li>
                    <li>Showing text in chart views</li>
                    <li>Presets for chart series colors</li>
                    <li>Adaptive resample to image</li>
                    <li>New Looking Glass plugin</li>
                    <li>New Geographical Map Plugin</li>
                    <li>New VRPlugin interactor styles</li>
                    <li>glTF 2.O reader available without a plugin</li>
                    <li>Many more improvements</li>
                </ul>
            </description>
        </release>
  </releases>
